d an indispensable guide for confronting future financial calamities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBank failureszUnited States. 0aBanks and bankingxState supervisionzUnited States. 0aFinancial criseszUnited States. 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009. 0aMonetary policyzUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic History.2bisacsh1 aAlvarez, Scott G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarr, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaxter, Thomas C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernanke, Ben S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernanke, Ben S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aClark, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeese, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDudley, William C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEnglish, William B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurman, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeithner, Timothy F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeithner, Timothy F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoyt, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJester, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKabaker, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKashkari, Neel T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohn, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrimminger, Michael H., econtributor.4ctb4https: